  "body": "- [ x] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen running `sudo truffle migrate` I get the following:\r\n```\r\nCould not connect to your Ethereum client with the following parameters:\r\n    - host       > 127.0.0.1\r\n    - port       > 7545\r\n    - network_id > 5777\r\n```\r\nHowever, my `truffle.config` looks like the following:\r\n```\r\nconst path = require(\"path\");\r\n\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  contracts_build_directory: path.join(__dirname, \"client/public/contract_abis\"),\r\n  networks: {\r\n    develop: {\r\n      host: \"127.0.0.1\",\r\n      port: 7546,\r\n      network_id: \"*\"\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  compilers: {\r\n    solc: {\r\n      version: \"^0.8.0\",    // Fetch exact version from solc-bin (default: truffle's version)\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThe migration should run effortlessly.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nWhen running `sudo truffle migrate` I get the following:\r\n```\r\nCould not connect to your Ethereum client with the following parameters:\r\n    - host       > 127.0.0.1\r\n    - port       > 7545\r\n    - network_id > 5777\r\n```\r\nThis is my ganache:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/30902582/169144438-0c5b6d17-8239-4e2d-a2ba-1d3b0da4a031.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: `Ubuntu 20.04.4 LTS`\r\n* NPM: `8.5.5`\r\n* Truffle/Solidity/Ganache/Node version (`truffle version`): ` `\r\n```\r\nTruffle v5.5.5 (core: 5.5.5)\r\nGanache v^7.0.3\r\nSolidity - ^0.8.0 (solc-js)\r\nNode v16.15.0\r\nWeb3.js v1.5.3\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nI appreciate your replies!",
