    "body": "Hi @marcpre, first, it's important not to use `sudo` when calling `truffle`. Second, it's possible that your network name `develop` is causing issues because you aren't specifying a network in your command.  To fix this, you could either add a `--network=develop` flag, or rename your network to `development`, which is the default network name. ",
